{{Expand English|Intelligent Design}}
'''智能設計論'''（{{lang-en|intelligent design}}，簡稱'''智設論'''、ID）是對[[神的存在|神的存在]]的宗教性[[逻辑论证|逻辑论证]]。儘管支持者認為智能設計論是一個「關於生命起源的科學理論」<ref name="Numbers 2006">{{cite book |last=Numbers |first=Ronald L. |authorlink=Ronald L. Numbers |year=2006 |origyear=Originally published 1992 as ''The Creationists: The Evolution of Scientific Creationism''; New York: [[Alfred_A._Knopf|Alfred A. Knopf]] |title=[[The_Creationists|The Creationists: From Scientific Creationism to Intelligent Design]] |edition=Expanded ed., 1st Harvard University Press pbk. |location=Cambridge, MA |publisher=[[Harvard_University_Press|Harvard University Press]] |isbn=0-674-02339-0 |lccn=2006043675 |oclc=69734583 |page=[https://archive.org/details/creationistsfrom0000numb/page/373 373]|quote=[ID] captured headlines for its bold attempt to rewrite the basic rules of science and its claim to have found indisputable evidence of a God-like being. Proponents, however, insisted it was 'not a religious-based idea, but instead an evidence-based scientific theory about life's origins – one that challenges strictly materialistic views of evolution.' Although the intellectual roots of the design argument go back centuries, its contemporary incarnation dates from the 1980s".}}</ref><ref name="Meyer 2005"/>，但其已遭主流科學界視為[[偽科學|偽科學]]<ref name="Boudry 2010">{{cite journal |last1=Boudry |first1=Maarten |authorlink1=Maarten Boudry |last2=Blancke |first2=Stefaan |last3=Braeckman |first3=Johan |authorlink3=Johan Braeckman |date=December 2010 |title=Irreducible Incoherence and Intelligent Design: A Look into the Conceptual Toolbox of a Pseudoscience |journal=[[The_Quarterly_Review_of_Biology|The Quarterly Review of Biology]] |location=Chicago, IL |publisher=[[University_of_Chicago_Press|University of Chicago Press]] |volume=85 |issue=4 |pages=473–482 |doi=10.1086/656904 |pmid=21243965 |url=https://biblio.ugent.be/publication/952482/file/6828579.pdf |access-date=2017-11-11 |archive-date=2017-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809035126/https://biblio.ugent.be/publication/952482/file/6828579.pdf |dead-url=no }} Article available from [https://biblio.ugent.be/publication/952482 Universiteit Gent] {{Wayback|url=https://biblio.ugent.be/publication/952482 |date=20150626115148 }}</ref><ref name="Pigliucci 2010">{{cite book |last1=Pigliucci |first1=Massimo |authorlink=Massimo Pigliucci |year=2010 |chapter=Science in the Courtroom: The Case against Intelligent Design |chapterurl=http://ncse.com/files/pub/evolution/Nonsenseonstilts.pdf |title=Nonsense on Stilts: How to Tell Science from Bunk |chapter-format=PDF |location=Chicago, IL |publisher=University of Chicago Press |isbn=978-0-226-66786-7 |lccn=2009049778 |oclc=457149439 |pages=160–186 |access-date=2017-11-11 |archive-date=2017-06-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170629184745/http://ncse.com/files/pub/evolution/Nonsenseonstilts.pdf |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref name="Young & Edis 2004">{{cite book |year=2004 |editor1-last=Young |editor1-first=Matt |editor2-last=Edis |editor2-first=Taner |title=Why Intelligent Design Fails: A Scientific Critique of the New Creationism |url=https://archive.org/details/whyintelligentde00youn_414 |location=New Brunswick, NJ |publisher=[[Rutgers_University_Press|Rutgers University Press]] |isbn=0-8135-3433-X |jstor=40072957 |lccn=2003020100 |oclc=59717533 |pages=[https://archive.org/details/whyintelligentde00youn_414/page/n211 195]-196}}</ref>。理論支持者宣稱：「與像[[自然選擇|自然選擇]]般無方向性進程相比，『某種超自然的智能設計了宇宙和生物的某些特徵』此一解釋明顯較佳<ref name="DI-topquestions">{{cite web |url=http://www.discovery.org/csc/topQuestions.php#questionsAboutIntelligentDesign |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=CSC - Top Questions: Questions About Intelligent Design: What is the theory of intelligent design? |website=[[Center_for_Science_and_Culture|Center for Science and Culture]] |publisher=[[Discovery_Institute|Discovery Institute]] |location=Seattle, WA |accessdate=2012-06-16 |archive-date=2016-03-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303170852/http://www.discovery.org/csc/topQuestions.php#questionsAboutIntelligentDesign |dead-url=no }}
*{{cite web |url=http://www.ideacenter.org/stuff/contentmgr/files/393410a2d36e9b96329c2faff7e2a4df/miscdocs/intelligentdesigntheoryinanutshell.pdf |title=Intelligent Design Theory in a Nutshell |year=2004 |publisher=[[Intelligent_Design_and_Evolution_Awareness_Center|Intelligent Design and Evolution Awareness Center]] |location=Seattle, WA |format=PDF |accessdate=2012-06-16 |archive-date=2012-05-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120503140812/http://www.ideacenter.org/stuff/contentmgr/files/393410a2d36e9b96329c2faff7e2a4df/miscdocs/intelligentdesigntheoryinanutshell.pdf |dead-url=no }}
*{{cite web |url=http://www.intelligentdesignnetwork.org/ |title=Intelligent Design |website=[[Intelligent_design_network|Intelligent Design network]] |location=Shawnee Mission, KS |publisher=Intelligent Design network, inc. |accessdate=2012-06-16 |archive-date=2018-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180121233703/http://www.intelligentdesignnetwork.org/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。」教育工作者、哲學家和科學界已證明智能设计論是[[創造論|創造論]]的一種形式、缺乏經驗證據支持，並且其假設沒一樣是能證驗或是正確的<ref name="ForrestMay2007Paper" /><ref name="consensus" /><ref name="NatureMethods2007">{{cite journal |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=December 2007 |title=An intelligently designed response |url=http://www.nature.com/nmeth/journal/v4/n12/full/nmeth1207-983.html |journal=[[Nature_Methods|Nature Methods]] |type=Editorial |publisher=[[Nature_Publishing_Group|Nature Publishing Group]] |location=London |volume=4 |issue=12 |page=983 |doi=10.1038/nmeth1207-983 |issn=1548-7091 |accessdate=2014-02-28 |ref=Nature Methods 2007 |archive-date=2014-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140309225030/http://www.nature.com/nmeth/journal/v4/n12/full/nmeth1207-983.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

支持者認為，智能设计論挑戰現代科學固有的方法论自然主义（methodological naturalism）<ref name="Meyer 2005">{{cite news |last=Meyer |first=Stephen C. |authorlink=Stephen C. Meyer |date=December 1, 2005 |title=Not by chance |url=http://www.canada.com/nationalpost/news/issuesideas/story.html?id=8f7f51f2-a196-4677-9399-46f4f17b5b61 |newspaper=[[National_Post|National Post]] |location=Don Mills, Ontario |publisher=[[Canwest|CanWest MediaWorks Publications Inc.]] |accessdate=2014-02-28 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060501021540/http://www.canada.com/nationalpost/news/issuesideas/story.html?id=8f7f51f2-a196-4677-9399-46f4f17b5b61 |archivedate=2006-05-01}}</ref><ref name="discovery">{{cite journal |last1=Meyer |first1=Stephen C. |last2=Nelson |first2=Paul A. |authorlink2=Paul Nelson (creationist) |date=May 1, 1996 |title=Getting Rid of the Unfair Rules |url=http://www.discovery.org/a/1685 |journal=Origins & Design |type=Book review |location=Colorado Springs, CO |publisher=[[Access_Research_Network|Access Research Network]] |accessdate=2007-05-20 |archive-date=2009-10-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091007094650/http://www.discovery.org/a/1685 |dead-url=yes }}
